result.execSummary:
The defendant Cornelius Marcus Bobo was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: Habitual Criminality Repeater, Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments, Habitual Criminality Repeater], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Cornelius Marcus Bobo in court, in custody.  Attorney Patrick Dennis Wait in court for Cornelius Marcus Bobo.  Prosecuting attorney Josh Milder in court for the State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: SD. 
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.    

AS TO COUNT 1:  Defendant ordered to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction, credit of 54 days time served, consecutive to count 2.

AS TO COUNT 2:  Defendant ordered to serve 60 DAYS with 60 DAYS time served.  THIS IS A TIME SERVED DISPOSITION, consecutive to count 1.

Court STAYED the count 1 and placed the defendant on probation for 18 months with the following conditions:

- Batters intervention program at the Alma Center
- Complete a mental health evaluation and comply with any recommended treatment.
- Alcohol and drug assessment and comply with any treatment deemed necessary by the department.
- Maintain absolute sobriety with random UAs.
- Complete a parenting class.
- No contact with victim.
- No use of possession of firearms.
- Full time work, school or a combination.
- Provide a DNA sample.

- Court WAIVES all non-mandatory costs, fees and surcharges.  Defendant to pay mandatory costs and surcharges (DNA and DV) during period of probation.  If unpaid a civil judgment will be ordered filed against the defendant.

Court advised Defendant of his right to seek postconviction relief.

Defendant Cornelius Marcus Bobo in court, in custody.  Attorney Patrick Dennis Wait in court for Cornelius Marcus Bobo.  Prosecuting attorney Josh Milder in court for the State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: SD. 
Matter scheduled for Jury Trial.  Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

AS TO COUNTS 1 AND 2: Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank. 

AS TO COUNTS 3 AND 4: Pursuant to plea negotiations and on State's motion, Court orders charge dismissed but read-in for sentencing purposes.

Court advised defendant due to this DV conviction s/he may never possess firearms or ammunition.
